      • Hashtable

        public Hashtable()
        Constructs a hashtable with the default hashing function. All hashtables constructed through the nullable constructor share the same default hashing function.

      • Hashtable

        public Hashtable(int initSize)
          throws IllegalArgumentException
        Constructs a hashtable with the default hashing function and a set initial capacity.
        Parameters:
        initSize - the initial capacity of the table.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the initial size is not positive

      • Hashtable

        public Hashtable(Function<E,Integer> hashFunction)
        Constructs a hashtable with a given hashing function that accepts the generic type E as the parameter and returns an integer. Unless the default hashing function is utilized, two objects that are considered equal (through instance or property equality) should return the same table value. As for two objects that do not return the same table value
        Parameters:
        hashFunction - the hashing function for this hashtable.

      • Hashtable

        public Hashtable(Function<E,Integer> hashFunction,
                 int initSize)
          throws IllegalArgumentException
        Constructs a hashtable with a given initial capacity and hashing function that accepts the generic type E as the parameter and returns an integer. Unless the default hashing function is utilized, two objects that are considered equal (through instance or property equality) should return the same table value. As for two objects that do not return the same table value
        Parameters:
        hashFunction - the hashing function for this hashtable.
        initSize - the initial capacity of the table.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the initial size is not positive

      • handleCollision

        private static void handleCollision(Object o,
                                    Object[] table,
                                    int originalIndex)
        Handles hashing collisions for a table by quadratically probing the table. This can loop forever if the table is already full.
        Parameters:
        o - the object to hash.
        table - the hash table.
        originalIndex - the index that the object was to be hashed to.

      • resizeTable

        private void resizeTable()
        Resizes the table and rehashes all non-null references in the previous table into the new table. The table will be double the previous size. Should only be called when count equals table.length

      • remove

        public final boolean remove(E element)
        Removes an element from the hashtable if it exists. Table is rehashed to account for hash collisions.
        Parameters:
        element - the element to remove.
        Returns:
        true if the element was removed

      • size

        public final int size()
        Returns:

      • clone

        public final Hashtable<E> clone()
        Clones this hash table. Any changes made to the previous hash table will not be reflected in the cloned table. Any changes made to the elements in the previous hash table, however, will be reflected in the cloned table if the changed element resides in both tables.
        Overrides:
        clone in class Object
        Returns:
        a clone of this hash table.
